methods.add:
Add a value to the set if its not already present.

*Overload 1*  
  :param value: (WeakIdentityHashSet.TYPE) - The value to add
  :return: (boolean) True if the value was added to the set
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param value: (WeakIdentityHashSet.TYPE) - The value to add
  :param valueReference: (java.lang.ref.WeakReference<? extendsWeakIdentityHashSet.TYPE>) - A re-usable WeakReference to value if already available, else null
  :return: (boolean) True if the value was added to the set
methods.forEach:
Invoke an action on each member of the set.

:param action: (java.util.function.Consumer<? superWeakIdentityHashSet.TYPE>) - The action to invoke

text:
An open-addressed identity hash set that only maintains weak references to its members.
 Only supports add(TYPE) and clear(). See WeakIdentityHashSet.Synchronized variant for concurrent usage.
